I would stick with the medical diet known within the profession as the "BRAT" diet. This is the nickname fo the diet often prescribed by nutritionists immediately following hospital release. B stands for bananas, R stands for "soft" boiled "white rice" with no seeds .. A stands for apple sauce .. and T stands for the inner central portion of a softly toasted slice of white bread. Each of these items .. when prepared as instructed .. will give nutrition with a minimum amount of chewing and digestion difficulties.
